BAO
\beta
AO=OE=x
2:1
OE=x
OB=2x
\angle OBA= 180^{\circ}-(120^{\circ}+\beta)=60^{\circ}-\beta
BOA
\frac{\sin\beta}{2x}=\frac{\sin(60^{\circ}-\beta)}{x}
\sin\beta=2\sin(60^{\circ}-\beta)
\sin \beta = 2\cos \beta\sin 60^{\circ}-2\cos 60^{\circ}\sin \beta
2\sin \beta=\sqrt{3} \cos \beta
\tan \beta= \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}
\beta=\arctan{\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}}
\angle BAC =\arctan{\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}}+60^{\circ}\approx 100.893^{\circ}
